article.story: KALAMAZOO, Mich. -- — Seth Hubbard had 19 points in Western Michigan's 77-58 victory against Miami (Ohio) on Tuesday night. Hubbard shot 5 for 12 (3 for 7 from 3-point range) and 6 of 7 from the free throw line for the Broncos (9-17, 6-7 Mid-American Conference). B. Artis White added 14 points while shooting 5 for 9, including 4 for 8 from beyond the arc, and he also had six rebounds. Owen Lobsinger had 12 points and shot 4 for 7, including 4 for 6 from beyond the arc. The Broncos stopped a six-game slide with the victory. The RedHawks (12-14, 6-7) were led by Anderson Mirambeaux, who recorded 19 points. Darweshi Hunter added eight points, nine rebounds and three steals for Miami. In addition, Evan Ipsaro had eight points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
